<br>
When I changed servers from emarr I noticed a drastic change in the enviroment. When I sent a petition IT WAS ANSWERED. It was always answered in a timely fashion. The gm/guides always were fun to interact with. I knew who they were and I knew their personality.<br>
<br>
You could bullshit with one another. They would keep you company on long camps. Kasmire although a lot of los hated him from /killing nag I felt he was a friend.<br>
<br>
The differential in customer service/fun is quite substantially different now. Guides/gm now do their &quot;job&quot; but are so stand offish you can't talk to them. Example someone is stuck in a gate.......does the guide say hello? no what does the guide do? he sits there and stares at us and um stares at us....then looks around hrm is that character really stuck? uh yeah.....then he summons him out.....then he gates off....can't even say thanks for the help just uh laters?<br>
<br>
When the guides/gm (old school)watched us it was like a boost to try harder stay up later not give up. I remember a night we were losing to inno lol anyways I can't remember the guides name but she/he was like &quot; you can't do it, not in your dreams&quot; I said I bet you a cleric BP they said no......anyways we won but there was alot more dialog.<br>
<br>
In all honesty I don't think that the no drop item should have been given to anyone. But I think that the players that whinned about it made us lose the best Gm I have encountered in 500+ levels of playing.<br>
<br>
Anyways I wish companies would understand that they get much farther in an enviroment when you can care about someone or something instead of just being able to do a &quot;job&quot;. I know who our gm is now but I don't know who one guide is............  <br>
<br>
Aanadyan/Deadone<br>
Level 60 warlock<br>
Legacy of Steel<br>
